            <h1>Human AI Interaction</h1>
            <div class="productlistBox">
              <img src="images/humanai.jpg" class="imgText bigImg" />
             Human-AI interaction studies and designs how humans and artificial intelligence (AI) systems communicate and collaborate. AI systems are computer programs that can perform tasks that usually require human intelligence, such as understanding natural language, recognizing images, making decisions, and learning from data. Human-AI interaction aims to create AI systems that are user-friendly, trustworthy, ethical, and beneficial for humans. It covers the broad spectrum of AI, including narrow AI, general AI and generative AI.
<br /><br />
Some of the topics and challenges that human-AI interaction addresses are:
                <br />
- How to make AI systems transparent and explainable so that users can understand how and why they work and what their limitations and uncertainties are.
                <br />
- How to design AI systems that are responsive and adaptive so that they can adjust to the userâ€™s needs, preferences, goals, and feedback.
                              <br />
- 
How to ensure AI systems are fair and accountable so that they do not discriminate, harm, or deceive users and respect their privacy, values, and rights.
                              <br />
- 
Using appropriate methods and metrics to evaluate AI systems and their impact on users, society, and the environment.
                              <br />
- 
Human-AI interaction is an interdisciplinary field that draws from various disciplines, such as computer science, psychology, sociology, design, and ethics. Human-AI interaction researchers and practitioners use multiple methods and tools, such as user research, prototyping, testing, and evaluation, to create and improve human-centered AI systems. The intention is to amplify and augment rather than displace human abilities.

